 infrastructure deployments that embed AWS compute and storage services within telecommunications providers' datacenters at the edge of the 5G network, so application traffic can reach application servers running in Wavelength Zones without leaving the mobile providers' network.`)})]}),links:[{label:e(`Regions and zones`),shortlink:`regions-azs`}]},[j9.availabilityZones]:{header:e(`Availability Zones`),content:(0,$.jsx)($.Fragment,{children:(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:e(`An Availability Zone is a distinct location within a Region that is insulated from failures in other Availability Zones, and provides inexpensive, low-latency network connectivity to other Availability Zones in the same Region.`)})}),links:[{label:e(`Regions and zones`),shortlink:`regions-azs`}]},[j9.localZones]:{header:e(`Local Zones`),content:(0,$.jsx)($.Fragment,{children:(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:e(`A Local Zone is an extension of an AWS Region in geographic proximity to your users. Local Zones have their own connections to the internet and support AWS Direct Connect, so resources created in a Local Zone can serve local users with very low-latency communications.`)})}),links:[{label:e(`Regions and zones`),shortlink:`regions-azs`}]},[j9.wavelengthZones]:{header:e(`Wavelength Zones`),content:(0,$.jsx)($.Fragment,{children:(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:e(`Wavelength Zones are AWS infrastructure deployments that embed AWS compute and storage services within telecommunications providers' datacenters at the edge of the 5G network, so application traffic can reach application servers running in Wavelength Zones without leaving the mobile providers' network.`)})}),links:[{label:e(`Regions and zones`),shortlink:`regions-azs`}]},[j9.defaultCreditSpecification]:{header:e(`Default credit specification`),content:(0,$.jsx)($.Fragment,{children:(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:e(`Unlimited is only available for T2, T3, T3a and T4g instances. Enabling Unlimited allows applications to burst beyond for as long as needed at any time. If the average CPU utilization is at or below he baseline, the hourly instance price automatically covers all usage. Otherwise, all usage above baseline is billed.`)})}),links:[{label:e(`Burstable performance instances`),shortlink:`instances/t2`}]},[j9.consoleExperiments]:{header:e(`Console experiments`),content:(0,$.jsx)($.Fragment,{children:(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:e(`If your account has a large number of snapshots, you can enable this feature to improve the experience of viewing snapshots in the Snapshots screen. If enabled, sorting will be disabled and filtering options will be limited.`)})}),links:[{label:e(`Amazon EBS snapshots`),shortlink:`ebs/snapshots`}]},[j9.resumeSession]:{header:e(`Resume console session`),content:(0,$.jsx)($.Fragment,{children:(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:e(`Open the console on a specific page or where you recently left off.`)})})},[j9.ec2SerialConsole]:{header:e(`EC2 Serial Console`),content:(0,$.jsxs)($.Fragment,{children:[(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:e(`The EC2 serial console provides access to your Amazon EC2 instance's serial port. You can use the serial console to troubleshoot boot, network configuration, and other issues. The serial console does not require your instance to have any networking capabilities. On the serial console, you can enter commands to an instance as if your keyboard and monitor are directly attached to the instance's serial port.`)}),(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:e(`Before you can use the serial console of an instance, you need to do the following:`)}),(0,$.jsxs)(`ul`,{children:[(0,$.jsx)(`li`,{children:e(`Launch the instance using a supported instance type.`)}),(0,$.jsx)(`li`,{children:e(`Configure access to the EC2 Serial Console.`)})]})]}),links:[{label:e(`EC2 Serial Console`),shortlink:`serial-console`}]},[j9.defaultlLifecyclePolicies]:{header:e(`Data Lifecycle Manager default policies`),content:(0,$.jsxs)($.Fragment,{children:[(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:e(`Data Lifecycle Manager default policies back up all volumes and instances in this Region that do not have recent backups. EBS snapshots and EBS-backed AMIs are created and retained based on the frequency set in the policy. These policies supplement your existing backup processes, and they will not result in duplicate backups.`)}),(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:(0,$.jsx)(y8,{content:e(`Use the <b>default policy for EBS snapshots</b> to create snapshots of all EBS volumes in this Region. You can optionally exclude boot volumes, specific volume types, or volumes that have specific tags.`)})}),(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:(0,$.jsx)(y8,{content:e(`Use the <b>default policy for EBS-backed AMIs</b> to create AMIs from all instances in this Region. You can optionally exclude instances that have specific tags.`)})})]}),links:[{label:e(`Data Lifecycle Manager default policies`),shortlink:`dlm/default-policies`}]},[j9.freeTierUsage]:{header:e(`EC2 Free Tier`),content:(0,$.jsxs)($.Fragment,{children:[(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:e(`The EC2 Free Tier lets you explore and experiment with EC2 at no cost. You get a limited amount of free access to EC2 for 12 months, starting when you sign up for an AWS account.`)}),(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:e(`Once your usage exceeds the Free Tier limits, or you’ve been an AWS customer for more than 12 months, we start charging you for usage. Therefore, it’s crucial that you keep track of your usage to avoid billing surprises.`)}),(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:e(`When we calculate your Free Tier usage, we count all the resources you’re using in all the AWS Regions. To easily locate and manage your EC2 resources across all the different AWS Regions, you can use the EC2 Global View.`)})]}),links:[{label:e(`AWS Free Tier`),longlink:YT(`free`,{region:nT.RegionUtils.getCurrentRegion().id})},{label:e(`Amazon EC2 Global View`),longlink:Qyn.getEC2Link(`global-view`)}]},[j9.autoscalingGroups]:{header:e(`Auto Scaling groups`),content:(0,$.jsxs)(`span`,{children:[(0,$.jsx)(`p`,{children:e(`The Resource tagging authorization setting determines whether